<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify">

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Formula Test Values Demo
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph>This sample compares the computed values of more than 160 formulas in WPF Grid with the same calculations from Excel.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center"><Image Source="Images\Image.png" Stretch="None" /></Paragraph>  

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Features
</Paragraph>
<List Margin="25,0,0,0">
<ListItem>
<Paragraph>The grid shows the relative difference, Excel value, computed value, and absolute value.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>It has the ability to display formulas in cells.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>It checks the next-compare-failure and set-error values.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>
</List>

<Paragraph FontWeight="Bold" FontFamily="Cambria" FontSize="16">
Interactive Features
</Paragraph>
<List Margin="25,0,0,0">

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>It checks the "Display Formulas" check box to display the respective formulas in their cells.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>To see the raw values in the cells of Column A, check the "Show Raw Values in Column A" check box.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

<ListItem>
<Paragraph>To set the relative error value and the error value format, use the "Relative Error" slider and change the values.</Paragraph>
</ListItem>

</List>

</FlowDocument>